alert.note: Alert for Holmes; Walton; Washington (Florida) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued February 09 at 9:52PM EST until February 09 at 10:30PM EST by NWS Tallahassee
info.description: The National Weather Service in Tallahassee has issued a * Severe Thunderstorm Warning for... Eastern Walton County in the Panhandle of Florida... Central Holmes County in the Panhandle of Florida... Northeastern Washington County in the Panhandle of Florida... * Until 930 PM CST. * At 852 PM CST, a severe thunderstorm was located 11 miles west of Bonifay, moving northeast at 30 mph. HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail. SOURCE...Radar indicated. IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage to roofs, siding, and trees. * Locations impacted include... Chipley, Bonifay, Ponce De Leon, Caryville, Westville, Five Points, Holmes County Airport, Whitehead Crossroads, Hulaw, Gritney, Poplar Head and Johnson Crossroads. TORNADO...POSSIBLE HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH
info.instruction: For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a building. Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.
